                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111/4121a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                            <gloss type="to">Diplomatic Officers</gloss> in Sweden, Norway, Denmark,
                        the Netherlands, and Spain</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Circular telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-10-10T13:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 10, 1916, 1 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Telegraph me briefly and as soon as possible what position has been taken by the
                    government to which you are accredited in regard to belligerent war or merchant
                    submarines visiting neutral ports or territorial waters. Cable substance of any
                    government decrees or decisions on this subject. I wish to obtain information as
                    to what restrictions, if any, have been imposed upon use of neutral ports and
                    waters by belligerent submarines, either before or since the Entente note of
                    August last respecting treatment of submarines by neutral powers.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
